      <body>
        <div>
            <pb facs="#TL-0082.jpg" n="part1_p082.jpg" xml:id="img_0081" corresp="https://id.acdh.oeaw.ac.at/tillich-lectures/part1_p082.jpg"/>
            
            <p facs="#facs_81_tr_2">
               <lb facs="#facs_81_tr_2_tl_1" n="N001"/>[78]
               <lb facs="#facs_81_tr_2_tl_2" n="N002"/><technology>in which, with the help of the principle of rationality, man has complete control over
               <lb break="no" facs="#facs_81_tr_2_tl_3" n="N003"/>the technical object, that the same thing can happen in the realms of independent life
               <lb break="no" facs="#facs_81_tr_2_tl_4" n="N004"/>in which man has no [longer] [<hi style="font-style: italic;">sic:</hi> has no the control] the control of complete rationality
               <lb break="no" facs="#facs_81_tr_2_tl_5" n="N005"/>and therefore the rationality element is breaking through, and has broken through, in the
               <lb break="no" facs="#facs_81_tr_2_tl_6" n="N006"/>middle of this century in a most terrifying way.
               <lb break="no" facs="#facs_81_tr_2_tl_7" n="N007"/>Now here you see--and this I must finish now, unfortunately--how fundamental
               <lb break="no" facs="#facs_81_tr_2_tl_8" n="N008"/>the religious problems of the technical realm are. We have only started to discuss them
               <lb break="no" facs="#facs_81_tr_2_tl_9" n="N009"/>and will go on next time.</technology>
            </p>
            
        </div>
